.panel#filterPanel
    h1 Filter Settings
    .optionsBody
        strong
            div Emotes
            .tooltipTrigger(data-tooltip-html='#FilterEmotesTooltipHTML') ?

        label.inline Filter Mode:
        .tooltipTrigger(data-tooltip-html='#emoteFilterModeTooltipHTML') ?
        p.line

        label.line.floatLeft
            input(type='radio', value='Blacklist', name='emoteFilterMode')
            | Blacklist
        label.line
            input(type='radio', value='Whitelist', name='emoteFilterMode')
            | Whitelist

        table#emoteFilterList

        hr

        strong
            div Websites
            .tooltipTrigger(data-tooltip-html='#FilterWebsitesTooltipHTML') ?

        label.inline Filter Mode:
        .tooltipTrigger(data-tooltip-html='#domainFilterModeTooltipHTML') ?
        p.line

        label.line.floatLeft
            input(type='radio', value='Blacklist', name='domainFilterMode')
            | Blacklist
        label.line
            input(type='radio', value='Whitelist', name='domainFilterMode')
            | Whitelist

        table#domainFilterList

    input.saveSettingsButton(type='button', value='Save Settings')

    #FilterEmotesTooltipHTML.tooltipHTML Allows you to disable or exclusively enable the rendering of certain emoticons.
        br
        b Emote Set:&nbsp;
        | The set of emoticons the given filter rule corresponds to, whether being Twitch.tv emotes, BetterTTV emotes, FrankerFaceZ emotes, or 7TV emotes.
        br
        b Rule Type:&nbsp;
        | Channel rules apply to all emotes belonging to the given channel. Emote rules apply only to the emote with the given name.
        br
        b Value:&nbsp;
        | Either the name of the channel or the name of the emote to filter, depending on the selected rule type.
    #emoteFilterModeTooltipHTML.tooltipHTML
        b Blacklist mode:&nbsp;
        | The emotes listed in the table directly below will not be rendered.
        br
        b Whitelist mode:&nbsp;
        | ONLY the emotes listed in the table below will be rendered.

    #FilterWebsitesTooltipHTML.tooltipHTML Allows you to disable or exclusively enable Global Twitch Emotes from running on certain websites. Asterisk wildcards supported.
        br
        b Example:
        br
        | "youtube.com" will trigger ONLY on the homepage of YouTube, while
        br
        | "youtube.com/*" will trigger on ALL addresses starting with youtube.com, such as the following:
        br
        a(href='https://www.youtube.com', target='_blank') https://www.youtube.com
        br
        a(href='https://www.youtube.com/feed/subscriptions', target='_blank') https://www.youtube.com/feed/subscriptions
        br
        a(href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IW--ZGJd5Fg', target='_blank') https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IW--ZGJd5Fg

    #domainFilterModeTooltipHTML.tooltipHTML
        b Blacklist mode:&nbsp;
        | Global Twitch Emotes will not run on websites listed in the table directly below.
        br
        b Whitelist mode:&nbsp;
        | Global Twitch Emotes will ONLY run on websites listed in the table directly below.